  <notepads>
    <notepad>
      <note>mw_lab_tests (
  lab_test_id          INT NOT NULL
  patient_id           INT NOT NULL,
  date_collected       DATE,
  test_type            VARCHAR(100),
  date_result_received DATE,
  date_result_entered  DATE,
  result_coded         VARCHAR(100),
  result_numeric       DOUBLE,
  result_exception     VARCHAR(100)
)</note>
      <xloc>1200</xloc>
      <yloc>32</yloc>
      <width>247</width>
      <heigth>197</heigth>
      <fontname>Ubuntu</fontname>
      <fontsize>11</fontsize>
      <fontbold>N</fontbold>
      <fontitalic>N</fontitalic>
      <fontcolorred>0</fontcolorred>
      <fontcolorgreen>0</fontcolorgreen>
      <fontcolorblue>0</fontcolorblue>
      <backgroundcolorred>255</backgroundcolorred>
      <backgroundcolorgreen>205</backgroundcolorgreen>
      <backgroundcolorblue>112</backgroundcolorblue>
      <bordercolorred>100</bordercolorred>
      <bordercolorgreen>100</bordercolorgreen>
      <bordercolorblue>100</bordercolorblue>
      <drawshadow>Y</drawshadow>
    </notepad>
    <notepad>
      <note>Viral Load is modeled as 4 independent observations
These are linked by encounter, not obs group currently. (MG: Aren't we storing in an obs group now?)
These observations are:
 * Sample taken for Viral Load = [True, null]
 * HIV viral load = &lt;Numeric result value>
 * Less than limit = &lt;Numeric result value>
 * Lower than Detection Limit = [True, null]
The "date_collected" is the obs date (eg. the grouping encounter date)
The "date_result_entered" is the obs date_created for either the
numeric viral load result, the less than limit, or the LDL observation.
If there's a numeric "Less than limit" observation, then it's recorded as a result exception as "&lt;[numeric result]"
If LDL is recorded as True, then "LDL" is recorded in result_exception</note>
      <xloc>32</xloc>
      <yloc>736</yloc>
      <width>762</width>
      <heigth>214</heigth>
      <fontname>Ubuntu</fontname>
      <fontsize>11</fontsize>
      <fontbold>N</fontbold>
      <fontitalic>N</fontitalic>
      <fontcolorred>0</fontcolorred>
      <fontcolorgreen>0</fontcolorgreen>
      <fontcolorblue>0</fontcolorblue>
      <backgroundcolorred>255</backgroundcolorred>
      <backgroundcolorgreen>205</backgroundcolorgreen>
      <backgroundcolorblue>112</backgroundcolorblue>
      <bordercolorred>100</bordercolorred>
      <bordercolorgreen>100</bordercolorgreen>
      <bordercolorblue>100</bordercolorblue>
      <drawshadow>Y</drawshadow>
    </notepad>
  </notepads>
